  <div class="sublist_thumbs"><h4><a href="http://www.npr.org/series/kitchen-window/">Kitchen Window</a></h4><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2012/01/17/145343357/bread-redux-dont-throw-out-those-stale-loaves"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/01/17/breadmain_sq.jpg?t=1326822173&amp;s=11" alt="It's not past its prime; give that old bread a second life in soup, salad, desserts and more."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2012/01/17/145343357/bread-redux-dont-throw-out-those-stale-loaves">Bread Redux: Don't Throw Out Those Stale Loaves</a></h3><p>It's not past its prime; give that old bread a second life in soup, salad, desserts and more.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2012/01/10/144966039/mediterranean-flatbreads-a-framework-for-flavor"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/01/10/cocahoney_sq.jpg?t=1326215063&amp;s=11" alt="Start with a thin oval of handmade dough. Top with veggies, herbs, meats, sweets &#x2014; anything goes."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2012/01/10/144966039/mediterranean-flatbreads-a-framework-for-flavor">Mediterranean Flatbreads: A Framework For Flavor</a></h3><p>Start with a thin oval of handmade dough. Top with veggies, herbs, meats, sweets â€” anything goes.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2012/01/03/144616121/a-toast-to-fresh-festive-cocktails"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2012/01/03/cocktailsmain_sq.jpg?t=1325631868&amp;s=11" alt="Using produce and herbs instead of syrupy mixers can cut calories and boost flavor."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2012/01/03/144616121/a-toast-to-fresh-festive-cocktails">A Toast To Fresh, Festive Cocktails</a></h3><p>Using produce and herbs instead of syrupy mixers can cut calories and boost flavor.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/12/27/144321788/baking-with-sweet-alternatives"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/12/27/sweetloafmain_sq.jpg?t=1325011192&amp;s=11" alt="Substituting for white sugar appeals to food writer Nicole Spiridakis' adventuresome spirit."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/12/27/144321788/baking-with-sweet-alternatives">Baking With Sweet Alternatives</a></h3><p>Substituting for white sugar appeals to food writer Nicole Spiridakis' adventuresome spirit.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/12/20/144025246/do-it-yourself-marshmallows"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/12/20/marshmallowscolor1_sq.jpg?t=1324411897&amp;s=11" alt="The silky confection lends itself to all sorts of flavors, from classic vanilla to pepper and chili."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/12/20/144025246/do-it-yourself-marshmallows">Do-It-Yourself Marshmallows</a></h3><p>The silky confection lends itself to all sorts of flavors, from classic vanilla to pepper and chili.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/12/13/143669613/jacques-pepin-an-american-from-paris"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/12/13/lamb_sq.jpg?t=1323816165&amp;s=11" alt="When he arrived in New York, the French master chef fell in love with the country."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/12/13/143669613/jacques-pepin-an-american-from-paris">Jacques Pepin: An American From Paris</a></h3><p>When he arrived in New York, the French master chef fell in love with the country.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/12/07/143251451/the-crackling-spices-of-indian-tempering"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/12/07/temperchicken1_sq.jpg?t=1323248583&amp;s=11" alt="A &lt;em&gt;tadka &lt;/em&gt;captures spices' essence and aroma in hot oil, infusing the final dish with distinct flavor."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/12/07/143251451/the-crackling-spices-of-indian-tempering">The Crackling Spices Of Indian Tempering</a></h3><p>A <em>tadka </em>captures spices' essence and aroma in hot oil, infusing the final dish with distinct flavor.</p></div></div><div class="bucket img"><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/29/142903042/cracking-the-poached-egg-code"><img src="http://media.npr.org/assets/img/2011/11/30/poachedeggsalad_sq.jpg?t=1322679956&amp;s=11" alt="When it comes to poaching eggs, practice makes perfect &#x2014; and opens up a world of luscious recipes."/></a><div class="bucketblock"><h3><a href="http://www.npr.org/2011/11/29/142903042/cracking-the-poached-egg-code">Cracking The Poached Egg Code</a></h3><p>When it comes to poaching eggs, practice makes perfect â€” and opens up a world of luscious recipes.</p></div></div><p class="more"><a href="http://www.npr.org/series/kitchen-window/">more</a></p></div>

